begin
reserve n for Nat;
reserve K for Field;
reserve M1 for (Matrix of n,K);
theorem
Th43: ((M1 is  invertible & ( ( M1 @ ) * M1 ) = ( 1. (K,n) )) iff M1 is  Orthogonal)
proof
A1: (( width M1 ) = n & ( len M1 ) = n) by MATRIX_1:24;
A2: ( width ( M1 @ ) ) = n by MATRIX_1:24;
A3: ( len ( M1 ~ ) ) = n by MATRIX_1:24;
A4: ( width ( M1 ~ ) ) = n by MATRIX_1:24;
thus ((M1 is  invertible & ( ( M1 @ ) * M1 ) = ( 1. (K,n) )) implies M1 is  Orthogonal)
proof
assume that
A5: M1 is  invertible
and
A6: ( ( M1 @ ) * M1 ) = ( 1. (K,n) );
A7: ( M1 ~ ) is_reverse_of M1 by A5,CKB15:def 1;
then ( ( ( M1 ~ ) * M1 ) * ( M1 ~ ) ) = ( ( ( M1 @ ) * M1 ) * ( M1 ~ ) ) by A6,CKB2:def 1;
then ( ( M1 ~ ) * ( M1 * ( M1 ~ ) ) ) = ( ( ( M1 @ ) * M1 ) * ( M1 ~ ) ) by A1,A4,A3,MATRIX_3:33;
then ( ( M1 ~ ) * ( M1 * ( M1 ~ ) ) ) = ( ( M1 @ ) * ( M1 * ( M1 ~ ) ) ) by A1,A3,A2,MATRIX_3:33;
then ( ( M1 ~ ) * ( 1. (K,n) ) ) = ( ( M1 @ ) * ( M1 * ( M1 ~ ) ) ) by A7,CKB2:def 1;
then ( ( M1 ~ ) * ( 1. (K,n) ) ) = ( ( M1 @ ) * ( 1. (K,n) ) ) by A7,CKB2:def 1;
then ( M1 ~ ) = ( ( M1 @ ) * ( 1. (K,n) ) ) by MATRIX_3:19;
then ( M1 ~ ) = ( M1 @ ) by MATRIX_3:19;
hence thesis by A5,CKB52:def 1;
end;

assume A8: M1 is  Orthogonal;
then M1 is  invertible by CKB52:def 1;
then A9: ( M1 ~ ) is_reverse_of M1 by CKB15:def 1;
( ( M1 @ ) * M1 ) = ( ( M1 ~ ) * M1 ) by A8,CKB52:def 1;
hence thesis by A8,A9,CKB2:def 1,CKB52:def 1;
end;
